    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>Hmmm, good question, Leah &#8211; and a tough one!  This is a pretty clean, healthy-tasting bread, and the honey is an important flavor component.  For your vegan version, my first thought would be to go with molasses, since it is a common ingredient in many other whole wheat breads.  I worry, though, that it might be too strong here, flavor-wise.  And as for maple syrup, I&#8217;d steer clear, since I&#8217;ve heard rumors that some brands, strangely enough, aren&#8217;t vegan-friendly.  Brown rice syrup would probably be just fine, although it lacks the lovely fragrance of both honey and molasses.  So all told, I think I&#8217;d try using a combination of molasses and brown rice syrup.  That way, you get some of the flavor of molasses, but you also get the mild, toasty sweetness of brown rice syrup.  I hope that helps&#8230;</></>Happy baking!</p>
    </div>

